1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper presents a method for automatic detection of calcifications in low-dose chest CT scans using convolutional neural networks. This falls under the domain of computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep neural networks for automatic calcium scoring in low dose chest CT scans. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents an AI-based method for automatic detection of calcifications in low-dose chest CT scans.
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may also fall under the domain of human-computer interaction as it involves the use of technology to aid in medical diagnosis.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of medical images, which may fall under the domain of multimedia.
